<p>Software Installation and First Connection
Note: If your PC contains a previous Wireless USB Suite driver installation, please perform
a proper uninstall procedure using the Windows Control Panel.</p>
<ol class="order-list">
<li class="order-list-item loose-list-item"><p>Ensure that the PC Adapter is unplugged from the PC.</p>
</li>
<li class="order-list-item loose-list-item"><p>Insert the installation CD in the CD ROM drive of the PC.</p>
</li>
<li class="order-list-item loose-list-item"><p>The installation CD Autorun start menu is displayed.</p>
</li>
<li class="order-list-item loose-list-item"><p>Select .Install Wireless USB Software.</p>
</li>
</ol>
<p>The installer offers two options:
 Option 1: Install Directly from CD - initiates the installation process from the CD.
 Option 2: Download latest software from the WEB - provides a link to a web address
where you can download software updates. If you choose this option, follow the
instructions provided on the software download page.</p>
<ol start="5" class="order-list">
<li class="order-list-item tight-list-item">If you select Option 1: Install Directly from CD, the install wizard begins installing the
Wireless USB software. The installation process may include more than one stage to
accommodate different drivers that are installed.</li>
</ol>
<p>User Guide Wireless USB Adapter Set R4.1</p>
<p>Proprietary Information Page 7</p>
<p>Vendor Logo</p>
<ol start="6" class="order-list">
<li class="order-list-item loose-list-item"><p>Choose your geographic region to comply with your local radio regulations. This setting
can be changed if needed once the software is installed.</p>
</li>
<li class="order-list-item loose-list-item"><p>Follow the onscreen instructions, and proceed by clicking Next&gt; when prompted, or by
approving authorization requests to continue the installation.</p>
</li>
<li class="order-list-item loose-list-item"><p>Once the installation procedure has finished, you are automatically returned to the
opening screen of the Autoplay menu.</p>
</li>
</ol>
